cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper analyzes the accuracy of citation data in two major databases, Web of Science and Scopus, which are commonly used in the fields of computer science, information retrieval, databases, cryptography, and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
